== The old drama ==

When chavscum was in its heyday (2004/early 2005) and hundreds of boring unoriginal [[Goth|gothics]] and [[Emo|emos]] thought that mass genocide was an acceptable solution for anyone who didn't like [[Shit|HIM]] (youth cultures are [[Serious_business|SERIOUS ISSUES!)]] and still do; leelard.net was a spin off forum which was orginaly a group for [[Gay|buddy buddy]] [[Counter-Strike|geeks and IT specialists]] and eventually majorly [[Butthurt]] [[Troll|trolls]], who took issue at aforementioned solution (I see the Jew) and got majorly [[Shit_nobody_cares_about|pissed off at threads mocking Drum and Bass]] so decided to fight the good fight by trolling them for the [[lulz]]. This noble deed resulted in several posters [[An_hero|leaving the forum]] which in retrospect was probably not a good thing, since most of these posters were capable of stringing a coherent sentence together; the remaining chavscum posters were a truly [[Lie|cosmopolitan bunch]] which meant that most of the threads became [[Faggot|fag fests]] involving angst and [[Unfunny|'the person above me']] game and long [[Boring|anecdotes]] about [[Lie|"being in the armed forces"]]. Despite the exodus of interesting, yet none the less [[Racist|bigoted]] posters, more and more [[Retard|'special posters']] arrived from their [[wank|Masturbation]] [[Masturbation|palaces]] which resulted in more trolls arriving, sniffing the scent of lulz on the internet, and promptly getting [[ban|banned]] but not without creating moar angst and moar gigalulz for leeladers. In a pathetic attempt to stem the horde of [[World_of_Warcraft|trolls]] the morbidly obese webmaster of Chavscum filtered out [[Lose|any words which he found objectionable]] which included names of previously [[Banhammered]] users, [[RL]] names, actual RL address and finally the url of other spin off forums including Leelad.net. Questioning this move would undoubtedly get you banned [[In_the_ass]] 
